property.description: Helper to manage Database List values (used like a Static list) of a class
Property of the class (must be a Database List!)
For Class designer: display or not the query to put on the "Hibernate Query" field of the property.
The document where the Database list entries will be saved. Default: the current document where is used this macro.

xwikidoc.content:
== Description ==
This application is an helper for simple users that allows them to design the fields of a DataBase List, which is used as a Static List that users can easily edit, without needing editing rights on the class.
== Usage ==
Just write: {{code}}{{dblist_manager property='..' wikiclass='..' showQuery='true|false' documentHandler='..' showTitle='true|false' /}}{{/code}}
Where :
* "##property##" is the property of the class to manage (must be a Database List!). * "##wikiclass##" is the class which contains the property. * "##showQuery##" //(optional)// is for the class designer: display or not the query to put on the "Hibernate Query" field of the property. (default: ##false##) * "##documentHandler##" //(optional)// is the document where the Database list entries will be saved. Default: the current document where is used this macro. * "##showTitle##" //(optional)// shows or not the title. (default: ##true##)
Then, in your class, you can create a //'Database List'// property and fill in the 'Hibernate Query' the content that you can display with //showQuery// parameter of the macro.
== Installation ==
Don't forget to add [[Macros.DBListManagerTranslations]] to your translation files.
== Example of use ==
1. In your class, add a Database List field [[image:Screen1.png||style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"]] 1. In the page where you want the user can customise it, call the macro: [[image:Screen2.png||style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"]] (or) [[image:Screen3.png||style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"]] 1. Get the Hibernate Query [[image:Screen4.png||style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"]] 1. Put it on the "Hibernate Query" field of your property in your class: [[image:Screen5.png||style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"]] 1. Add some values using the macro [[image:Screen6.png||style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"]] 1. Enjoy the results, when you create an object of your class: [[image:Screen7.png||style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"]]
